    "3 Comparison between MAT and R-MAT self-attention modules.",
    "The self-attention block comprises scaling and applying softmax.",
    "In MAT, distance and adjacency matrices are outside the self-attention block, while in R-MAT all matrices are mixed within the self-attention.",
    "Moreover, all atom-pair embeddings are collected in one matrix that is also multiplied by queries and keys information about the models and datasets used in this benchmark is given in Additional file 1.Table 3 shows that R-MAT outperforms other methods in 3 out of 6 tasks.",
